13/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Work on the Olympic sites will be completed in time for the Games in August, the chief inspector of the International Olympic Committee said Wednesday (12 May).
"No single project is at risk and we know that everything will be ready on time," Denis Oswald said at a press briefing.
In other news, Greece unveiled the first ever-Olympic commemorative coins to be denominated in euros.
The coin depicts the popular figure of the discus thrower.
An estimated 50 million two-euro coins will go on sale Thursday and will be legal tender in all countries where the euro is the official currency.
(Reuters, AFP, Sunday Times, ANA, MOA - 12/05/04)
